WEBVTT

00:16.578 --> 00:42.354
a list of all of the good things you've done for me Lord I've never been one to complain but right now I'm lost but I can't find my way my worlds come up

00:44.578 --> 00:53.830
is breaking my heart, but it helps to know your heart is breaking too.

00:54.211 --> 00:57.415
When I cry, you cry.

00:57.455 --> 01:00.999
When I hurt, you hurt.

01:01.780 --> 01:08.129
When I've lost someone, it takes a piece of you too.

01:08.970 --> 01:12.274
When I fall on my face,

01:14.754 --> 01:26.674
For nothing breaks your heart What tears you apart like when I cry?

01:45.506 --> 02:14.738
There's never been a time in my life Where so much has stayed There's so much to lose But I trust it to you You'll bring me through And it helps me to know That I'm not alone When I cry

02:15.650 --> 02:45.170
When I hurt, you hurt When I lost someone It takes a piece of you too And when I fall on my face You fill me with grace That's nothing great so hard Or tells you apart Like when I cry

02:54.562 --> 03:24.434
You want to make the blind to see You look through all of heaven and eternity And through it all you some be When I cry, you cry When I hurt, you hurt

03:24.802 --> 03:31.711
And when I've lost someone, it takes a piece of you too.

03:32.272 --> 03:43.947
When I fall on my face, you fill me with praise.

03:45.269 --> 03:52.498
Nothing breaks your heart or tears you apart.

03:54.306 --> 04:00.306
Like when I cry

04:27.586 --> 04:32.230
song, beautiful, beautiful singing.

04:33.211 --> 04:33.832
Good morning.

04:37.055 --> 04:38.897
Well, we're all the people today.

04:39.217 --> 04:42.480
They knew I'm going to preach and they left all of them.

04:44.362 --> 04:45.042
They vanished.

04:45.983 --> 04:53.010
Well, bless them all, vacation time, visitation time, seeing friends time.

04:55.012 --> 04:57.234
We hope to see them back very soon.

05:00.546 --> 05:15.227
Today is the last day as we worship the last or the final service of 2025.

05:15.387 --> 05:17.009
Dear life's that.

05:20.314 --> 05:28.626
And time to reflect about the past year.

05:30.754 --> 05:34.278
And time so many people make resolutions.

05:38.462 --> 05:40.424
And they look with hope to the future.

05:43.448 --> 05:50.936
Today, what I'd like to cover with you by the will of God.

05:53.038 --> 05:58.043
The past, the present, and the future.

06:00.005 --> 06:00.626
Briefly.

06:01.730 --> 06:04.913
so we can go home one time.

06:04.933 --> 06:08.957
I want to read a couple of verses that are identical.

06:10.178 --> 06:22.911
Romans 831 says, what then shall we say if God is with us who can be against us?

06:23.992 --> 06:29.778
I have another version which I like and it says,

06:29.986 --> 06:36.715
If God is on our side, who can ever be against us?

06:39.078 --> 06:51.195
Looking backward, we have few days left from this year, and it's comforting to know how the Lord has dealt with us.

06:53.838 --> 06:59.506
Reflections reminds us of what He the Lord has done.

07:00.578 --> 07:06.666
And there are some questions that we should ask ourselves.

07:09.110 --> 07:11.012
What am I most thankful for?

07:11.072 --> 07:17.120
Did I live to honor him the past year?

07:19.443 --> 07:22.688
Did I obey him when I clearly heard his voice?

07:24.931 --> 07:26.313
Did I love him enough?

07:28.476 --> 07:30.258
Did I support my church?

07:31.906 --> 07:35.471
Was I a good representative of true Christianity?

07:38.354 --> 07:51.511
We ponder and we review God's dealings with us and it's humbling and we should be very thankful.

07:56.998 --> 08:00.402
When we read about the Prophet,

08:01.538 --> 08:04.521
what he said to the nation of old.

08:06.543 --> 08:11.267
Thus far, thus far, the Lord has helped us.

08:11.568 --> 08:12.108
Didn't he?

08:13.269 --> 08:13.970
We're all here.

08:14.991 --> 08:15.472
Didn't he?

08:17.554 --> 08:26.682
Looking back on the past year, we remember people getting saved and a revival in the hearts of our family.

08:27.043 --> 08:30.386
We also see growth in spirituality.

08:33.250 --> 08:35.592
and in numbers.

08:37.474 --> 08:40.157
We see God's power in answering prayers.

08:44.020 --> 08:55.952
How many requests and supplications has he heard and answered individually and collectively?

08:57.513 --> 09:02.738
We had ups, some ups, and we had downs, and thank God,

09:03.106 --> 09:05.069
The ups were greater than the downs.

09:07.732 --> 09:12.619
We had a couple of saints that went before us to glory.

09:13.961 --> 09:21.271
We are blessed and thankful for God's keeping as we transit this wilderness.

09:24.195 --> 09:31.826
Yes, we humbly acknowledge God's presence with us, and we give him all

09:32.066 --> 09:38.933
their credits for his love, his mercy, and guidance on this journey.

09:39.934 --> 09:42.356
Let's take courage and go on.

09:44.038 --> 09:46.640
The past is God's, right?

09:47.581 --> 09:53.226
The future is God's and his power is greater than all.

09:55.268 --> 10:01.234
Now, this is what I want to spend some time looking in order.

10:02.946 --> 10:04.528
We looked a little bit backward.

10:08.194 --> 10:10.156
And we don't want to say it was a bad year.

10:10.517 --> 10:12.620
No, not at all.

10:12.640 --> 10:14.102
It's always a good year.

10:16.165 --> 10:23.175
Looking inward, so many cannot handle facing their present life.

10:26.139 --> 10:29.384
For them, the present is the norm for the future.

10:29.985 --> 10:30.866
They don't want to move.

10:32.066 --> 10:37.011
They say we've been living for a while in this mode and we need no change.

10:38.713 --> 10:44.760
There's too many things to do to get better, so better stay the way we are.

10:46.201 --> 10:47.323
Why rock the boat?

10:49.084 --> 10:50.326
Why start anew?

10:51.227 --> 10:52.188
Why the change?

10:53.209 --> 10:57.874
And you hear them saying, if it ain't broke, don't fix it.

11:01.218 --> 11:04.562
They are saying what we have is the best.

11:06.925 --> 11:08.126
We can't do any better.

11:10.109 --> 11:11.571
So don't try to improve it.

11:13.433 --> 11:16.697
Stay as you will or as you are.

11:18.679 --> 11:20.902
They're stuck in their ways.

11:22.524 --> 11:23.445
What an attitude.

11:24.847 --> 11:30.674
It has been suggested that the mark of many church people today

11:31.618 --> 11:36.525
is that they are chosen.

11:38.487 --> 11:42.553
They are not chosen, but they are frozen.

11:51.606 --> 11:52.847
What's the challenge there?

11:55.851 --> 11:57.714
What should be done now?

12:00.290 --> 12:02.693
We have many opportunities to seize.

12:03.013 --> 12:09.120
The Bible says seize the opportunities before the Lord comes.

12:10.642 --> 12:18.170
The Bible says in 2 Timothy 4, 2, Paul writing to Timothy.

12:19.151 --> 12:26.459
He says, preach the word, be ready in Caesar and out of Caesar.

12:27.581 --> 12:28.882
Now is the time.

12:29.538 --> 12:33.143
to begin with what the future holds.

12:35.526 --> 12:58.258
Someone wrote, the life of a Christian can be described in one of four ways as a journey, as a battle, as a pilgrimage,

12:59.554 --> 13:01.937
and as a race, four things.

13:04.901 --> 13:08.806
And the writer says, select your own metaphor.

13:11.489 --> 13:18.158
But the necessity to finish is always the same in any of these categories.

13:26.368 --> 13:28.050
For a flight,

13:29.474 --> 13:30.315
is a journey.

13:31.217 --> 13:33.621
It must be completed, right?

13:36.205 --> 13:39.871
If life is a battle, it must be finished.

13:42.315 --> 13:46.722
If life is a pilgrimage, it must be concluded.

13:48.005 --> 13:51.691
And if life is a race, it must be won.

13:51.711 --> 13:56.178
And we are in a race.

13:59.074 --> 14:01.336
And we cannot give in to defeat.

14:05.080 --> 14:13.108
We are more than conquerors, the Bible says, through him, not on our own, through him, who loved us.

14:16.612 --> 14:17.733
And then what do we do?

14:19.294 --> 14:20.976
What do we say to this?

14:23.078 --> 14:23.919
Are we disturbed?

14:23.979 --> 14:24.279
No.

14:25.340 --> 14:27.122
By any change, not.

14:30.722 --> 14:41.057
Are we afraid of the difficulties we are facing today, and we might face every day in the future?

14:43.200 --> 14:55.677
Paul writes in Romans 831, if God is on our side, who can ever be against us?

14:56.879 --> 14:58.962
If God is on our side.

15:02.690 --> 15:04.512
How are we going to face the future?

15:07.236 --> 15:08.197
We're looking within.

15:10.039 --> 15:11.080
What are we going to do?

15:11.240 --> 15:12.482
We don't know what's happening.

15:12.502 --> 15:14.705
We don't know what's coming our way.

15:15.726 --> 15:20.171
But if God is on our side, we can.

15:20.372 --> 15:21.733
Who can be against us?

15:23.916 --> 15:32.306
To those who are comfortable being stagnant, set in their ways, and are stuck

15:36.002 --> 15:38.484
for almost good.

15:42.608 --> 15:43.830
They're not willing to move.

15:45.871 --> 15:49.475
They're not moving forward.

15:51.337 --> 15:55.301
Compromise and stagnancy lead to defeat, my friends.

15:56.822 --> 16:05.170
We follow a victorious leader whom we obey and move forward to win the race.

16:06.018 --> 16:08.140
The Lord ordered his disciples.

16:09.742 --> 16:12.745
Before he left, he got them all together.

16:13.305 --> 16:15.588
Before he left, I said, go.

16:15.608 --> 16:18.931
That's it.

16:19.351 --> 16:19.652
Go.

16:19.692 --> 16:23.756
Preach, teach, and baptize.

16:33.385 --> 16:34.226
The word go.

16:37.730 --> 16:41.393
is against stagnancy, the opposite of stagnancy.

16:42.434 --> 16:50.622
The opposite in sitting, I know, or we know it's too difficult.

16:51.323 --> 16:59.070
We are happy in our ways, and we keep it as is we pray that nothing will change.

17:01.052 --> 17:03.214
We are living in a changing world.

17:06.197 --> 17:07.538
Everything changes.

17:10.082 --> 17:16.572
And so many times we catch ourselves saying, well, those were their good old days.

17:17.234 --> 17:19.537
Things change.

17:22.322 --> 17:24.846
And we have to acclimate ourselves to that.

17:25.707 --> 17:27.450
And we have to accept the change.

17:27.971 --> 17:29.674
And we are not alone.

17:30.815 --> 17:37.426
As we said, if God is for us, who can be against us?

17:38.338 --> 17:39.800
That's an encouraging word.

17:40.000 --> 17:47.551
I want to encourage you this morning and let you know that God is with us.

17:47.651 --> 17:52.838
When he sent his disciples to go, he said, go.

17:52.858 --> 17:53.098
Go.

17:53.599 --> 17:54.921
I'm courting the Bible.

17:56.423 --> 18:01.750
Go and preach and teach.

18:04.294 --> 18:07.538
And lo, I am with you.

18:08.962 --> 18:09.603
for how long?

18:11.545 --> 18:14.648
Can you tell me for how long?

18:15.049 --> 18:15.509
Thank you.

18:16.330 --> 18:16.791
Always.

18:17.512 --> 18:19.134
I'm with you, always.

18:19.154 --> 18:24.379
He didn't say, I'm with you as long as you behave.

18:24.399 --> 18:24.580
No.

18:25.381 --> 18:32.949
I'm with you for like 90% of my own thinking.

18:33.490 --> 18:35.012
I'm with you for 90% care.

18:36.493 --> 18:37.234
Will that work?

18:43.650 --> 18:46.614
I'm with you in summer or winter.

18:48.276 --> 18:53.964
No, he is with us all ways.

18:56.727 --> 19:01.914
Suppose you're in a very bad mood and you lose it.

19:04.057 --> 19:04.958
Is God with you?

19:06.020 --> 19:07.061
Will he be with you?

19:08.303 --> 19:13.650
I want to tell you when I got stuck on this one.

19:14.050 --> 19:20.277
He said, when you don't love God that day, do you think God is still with you?

19:25.643 --> 19:29.748
When you lose it with the family, if still God loves you.

19:33.732 --> 19:34.633
Hey, disciples.

19:36.595 --> 19:42.482
And these disciples did not say to the Lord, hey,

19:43.938 --> 19:45.440
This is a great task.

19:47.102 --> 19:49.004
We're not equipped to do it.

19:50.326 --> 19:52.509
We did not go to theology school.

19:53.810 --> 19:57.635
We are uneducated, bunch of fishermen.

19:58.456 --> 20:00.398
One of them is a tax collector.

20:03.102 --> 20:07.127
But they had the word of God.

20:08.048 --> 20:10.912
I am with you always.

20:12.413 --> 20:12.914
God,

20:13.282 --> 20:15.265
Never lost a battle.

20:17.088 --> 20:18.430
He never lost a war.

20:19.151 --> 20:20.032
You're going to go.

20:20.252 --> 20:26.862
You're going to face many difficulties, oppositions from everywhere.

20:28.224 --> 20:30.267
I am always with you.

20:34.614 --> 20:37.378
He didn't say, I'm with you most of the times.

20:39.461 --> 20:40.082
No.

20:42.242 --> 20:43.744
I am with you always.

20:45.967 --> 20:46.869
Remember this.

20:49.933 --> 20:58.705
This is the attitude that we should be in, that looking within, we have a new year coming.

21:00.628 --> 21:07.698
And if we face that new year with a defeated attitude,

21:10.722 --> 21:13.266
we might not win the race.

21:13.286 --> 21:22.439
We win the race with Jesus Christ because he said, I am with you.

21:22.459 --> 21:30.470
Don't let anything pull you down as looking within what I said and keep going.

21:32.473 --> 21:38.482
The past and its failures shall not hinder

21:41.026 --> 21:42.007
us at all.

21:43.249 --> 21:53.781
Paul wrote to the Philippians, quoting, brethren, I do not count myself to have apprehended or arrived.

21:54.642 --> 22:07.858
But one thing I do, forgetting things which are behind and reaching forward to those things which are.

22:10.498 --> 22:12.761
Many people would like to live in the past.

22:13.642 --> 22:17.586
And many people would like to say, well, an ugly year.

22:19.168 --> 22:20.210
Forget about it.

22:20.950 --> 22:24.715
We don't want to forget about it the past year.

22:24.895 --> 22:25.235
Why?

22:25.776 --> 22:31.163
Because we had many good experiences.

22:33.545 --> 22:35.127
We had many good victories.

22:35.868 --> 22:37.490
But we cannot live on that.

22:40.002 --> 22:53.759
Thank God, and leave it there, and God will lead us into new victories and new life through Him who never left us.

22:56.202 --> 23:08.357
Brethren, I do not count myself that I have arrived, but one thing I do, I forget what's behind.

23:08.377 --> 23:09.298
But I am

23:09.538 --> 23:18.346
I have learned and I will apply it for the next year.

23:19.287 --> 23:23.291
We shall talk about it next Sunday.

23:25.913 --> 23:39.186
I tell you, Church, I am convinced myself that relying on God and the direction of the Holy Spirit will guide us through rain or sunshine.

23:39.746 --> 23:42.290
until we reach the eternal shore.

23:45.294 --> 23:53.487
No matter what, we will go forward as long as his presence is with us.

24:02.901 --> 24:08.850
This is what I thought about in my little office.

24:10.274 --> 24:11.595
to bring your attention.

24:13.077 --> 24:15.479
Let us not live in the past.

24:17.841 --> 24:18.682
It's gone.

24:21.024 --> 24:22.385
Have we learned some lessons?

24:23.146 --> 24:25.488
Let's apply them for now.

24:26.449 --> 24:32.094
Let's look within and see what kind of attitude I am going to look forward with.

24:35.738 --> 24:36.919
The past is past.

24:37.880 --> 24:40.242
The present, this is, I'm getting ready.

24:42.626 --> 24:50.195
the future is coming and the Lord would have us to walk through, not without Him.

24:50.896 --> 25:00.347
Remember, we are going to work with Him who is with us all the ways, all the ways.

25:04.172 --> 25:12.562
Next week, we are going to look together at the challenges and the blessings ahead of us.

25:13.762 --> 25:15.123
one important fact.

25:17.065 --> 25:29.918
We need to realize, as Christians, believers in the Lord Jesus Christ as our Savior, we're not on the way to death.

25:32.861 --> 25:35.623
Remember, we're not on the way to death.

25:37.846 --> 25:38.847
Don't think of that.

25:39.647 --> 25:42.450
Instead, through Christ, we are on the way

25:42.562 --> 25:52.272
to an abundant life, to an eternal life, to life to be with the Lord Jesus Christ forever and ever.

25:52.793 --> 25:54.955
The end is not six feet under.

25:55.876 --> 26:03.884
We're looking as Dave Thompson told me once, he said, I am, he was 97 years old.

26:04.385 --> 26:09.490
He said, I'm not looking for the undertaker, I'm looking for the upper ticker.

26:20.290 --> 26:44.176
Let's continue serving as those who do believe and live so as to persuade others to believe that the Lord Jesus Christ is the only Savior, the only God, and He is the only way to salvation.

26:44.196 --> 26:44.977
Let's do that.

26:47.941 --> 26:49.202
And if there's someone here,

26:51.810 --> 27:00.404
who doesn't know the Lord Jesus Christ as Savior.

27:01.145 --> 27:02.026
I invite you.

27:03.308 --> 27:13.504
It's scary to go through another year without the Lord Jesus Christ, without His presence.

27:17.230 --> 27:17.871
It's scary.

27:17.891 --> 27:19.794
So come to Jesus.

27:20.898 --> 27:26.206
and He will save you and give you peace, eternal peace.

27:26.707 --> 27:40.687
So when you look and say, I am going to look at our future, you look at the future with faith, with hope that you are going to live and see Him one day.

27:41.168 --> 27:45.575
Remember, we are not looking for death.

27:46.095 --> 27:48.519
We are looking to win the race.

27:49.340 --> 27:50.642
Next week, we'll cover it.

27:51.330 --> 27:58.079
And hopefully, all those who are traveling on vacation will be back.

27:58.179 --> 28:04.107
And all of us will be here to come and honor God and live for him.

28:05.008 --> 28:06.430
That's my message.

28:06.450 --> 28:07.251
God bless you.

28:07.811 --> 28:09.053
Have a happy New Year.

28:09.814 --> 28:19.026
And see you next week, bright and let's buy our heads for a prayer.

28:21.314 --> 28:22.215
Thank you, Father.

28:24.319 --> 28:49.778
Thank you for allowing us to spend the last Sunday of the whole year of this year together in your house and help us, Lord, to be open-minded and face the coming year with an open heart, with joy knowing

28:51.042 --> 28:59.113
that as long as you're with us, and your presence is with us, we shall reach the eternal shore.

28:59.934 --> 29:04.700
Bless each and everyone, and thank you for each and every family.

29:05.622 --> 29:12.291
Bless them, keep them healthy, and we pray that they will have a great and happy New Year.

29:13.452 --> 29:15.635
Dismiss us, we pray in Jesus' name.

29:16.216 --> 29:16.536
Amen.

29:17.898 --> 29:20.722
Thank you for listening to me, and may God bless you.

29:20.962 --> 29:22.483
Enjoy the new year.

